 Design a Parking Lot System

 Driver(vehicle) --> Parking Lot entry --> Park Vehicle --> Parking Lot exit

 Parking Lot entry
 1. User Input = createTicket(licencePlate, vehicleType) --> Ticket(id, entry_time, vehicleType)
    - process : on basis of vehicleType --> check available ParkingSlot --> create a Parking slot
            --> create a Ticket --> send Ticket to the driver




 Parking Lot exit
 - exit_time



 Interviewer Possible Questions?

    Q1. For parking lot LLD system Design, why we need a licencePlateNumber?

    1. Unique Identification of a Vehicle
    - The **licensePlateNumber** acts as a **unique key** to identify each vehicle.
    - Without it, if two white hatchbacks park at the same time, youâ€™d have no idea which one belongs to which ticket.
    - Think of it as the `primary key` for your `Vehicle` entity.

    2. Integration with Real Systems
    - Cameras capture license plates automatically.
    - The system opens gates or calculates fees automatically.

    3. Fraud Prevention and Enforcement
    - Imagine someone loses their ticket and claims, I came just 5 minutes ago!â€ ğŸ˜‡
    - Your system can check: > â€œActually, your license plate entered 3 hours ago.â€ â°
    -  It also helps detect **blacklisted vehicles**, **stolen cars**, or track **violations**.
